#Text=Four men go before Hungarian court after 71 found dead in lorry
#Text=Saturday , August 29 , 2015
#Text=Four foreign men have today gone before a court in Hungary on suspicion of people smuggling .
#Text=Their detention relates to Thursday 's discovery of a lorry full of corpses in Austria .
#Text=The death toll was yesterday finalised at 71 .
#Text=Today 's hearing took place at the Palace of Justice in Kecskemet , pictured here from file .
#Text=Image : Tothsandor92 .
#Text=The lorry had been abandoned since Wednesday on the hard shoulder of the " Eastern Motorway " , near the Hungarian border .

column1: #Text=Roadworkers became suspicious of dark liquid seeping from the vehicle , and responding police found the bodies .
#Text=Initial police estimates were that 20 – 50 were suffocated in the back of the lorry which was near Parndorf .
#Text=The arrested men are thought to include the vehicle 's owner and at least two drivers .
#Text=Three are Bulgarian and one is from Afghanistan .
#Text=Criminal suspects in Hungary can generally be held for 72 hours before charge but prosecutors , citing the seriousness of the case , want the period extended .
#Text=Extradition to Austria is possible .
#Text=Of the 71 dead , 59 are men , eight are women , and four are children .
#Text=The children are thought to be aged three , eight , and ten years , alongside an eighteen-month-old baby .

#Text=" There was also a Syrian travel document found " police spokesman Hans Peter Doskozil told journalists " so of course our first assumption is that these people were migrants , and likely a group of Syrian migrants .

#Text=The stowaways also appeared with a line through them alongside the word  imigranti " and the site www . imigranti . sk in one corner .

column1: #Text=On the other side was Hyza 's logo .
#Text=Imigranti . sk is also unavailable .
#Text=Police today found 26 migrants in a lorry near Braunau am Inn , Austria .
#Text=The driver , from Romania , refused to stop for police and was arrested following a chase .
#Text=Police said three children were hospitalised for " severe dehydration " .
#Text=Found near the German border , the migrants were from Afghanistan , Syria , and Bangladesh .
